      "message": "The additional const is necessary. In the original code, \n\n    table[0] \u003d nullptr;\n\nwas perfectly valid and would mutate the passed-in static array. (As you can imagine, this is a very undesirable property.)\nWith constexpr, the array itself is now const and cannot be mutated.\nAs such, removing the const leads to a compile error:\n\n  ../../src/utils/SkParse.cpp:251:9: error: no matching function for call to \u0027lookup_str\u0027\n    if (lookup_str(str, gYes, SK_ARRAY_COUNT(gYes)))\n        ^~~~~~~~~~\n  ../../src/utils/SkParse.cpp:238:13: note: candidate function not viable: no known conversion \n  from \u0027const char *const [3]\u0027 to \u0027const char **\u0027 for 2nd argument\n  static bool lookup_str(const char str[], const char** table, int count)\n              ^",
